arXiv:2407.20551v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: By analyzing a data sample of $e^+e^-$ collisions with center-of-mass energy $\sqrt{s}=3.773$ GeV, corresponding to an integrated luminosity of $7.9~m {fb}^{-1}$ collected with the BESIII detector operating at the BEPCII collider, we study semileptonic decays of the $D^{0(+)}$ mesons into the axial-vector meson $b_1(1235)$ via the decay $b_1(1235)	o \omega\pi$. The decay $D^0	o b_1(1235)^-e^{+}
u_{e}$ is observed with a significance of 5.2$\sigma$ after considering systematic uncertainty, while evidence for the decay $D^+	o b_1(1235)^0 e^+
u_e$ is obtained with a 3.1$\sigma$ significance. The product branching fractions are determined to be ${\mathcal B}(D^0	o b_{1}(1235)^-e^{+}
u_{e})	imes {\mathcal B} (b_1(1235)^-	o \omega \pi^-) = (0.72\pm0.18^{+0.06}_{-0.08})	imes10^{-4}$ and ${\mathcal B}(D^+	o b_{1}(1235)^0e^{+}
u_{e})	imes {\mathcal B} (b_1(1235)^0~	o \omega \pi^0) = (1.16\pm0.44\pm0.16)	imes10^{-4}$, where the first uncertainties are statistical and the second systematic. The ratio of their partial decay widths is determined to be $ rac{\Gamma(D^0	o b_{1}(1235)^-e^{+}
u_{e})}{2\Gamma(D^+	o b_{1}(1235)^0e^{+}
u_{e})}=0.78\pm0.19^{+0.04}_{-0.05}$, which is consistent with unity, predicted by isospin invariance, within uncertainties.
